 missions in high threat Outside Continental United States (OCONUS) locations.

 Sedans and cargo/utility trucks are armored to various levels of protection and are on platforms of varying sizes and gross vehicle weights, dependent upon the level of threat and the operating environment.
 These vehicles are generically referred to as either Commercial Heavy Armored Vehicles (CHAVs) or Commercial Light Armored Vehicles (CLAVs).$$, NULL, $$Exhibit P-40, Budget Line Item Justification: PB 2027 Navy                                                                                                                     Date: April 2026
