 Description:
 This budget line includes NEXT GENERATION SQUAD WEAPON AMMUNITION


 (E06002) CTG 6.8MM GENERAL PURPOSE ROUND (M1186) is a 6.8mm Ball Cartridge, General Purpose (GP) ammunition packed in cartons for use in the Next Generation Squad Weapons (NGSW) M7
 Rifle/XM8 Carbine. The GP Ball Cartridge has a steel penetrator and non-lead slug surrounded by a copper jacket. This ammunition is intended for use against personnel and light-armored targets. The GP
 ammunition is a training standard item used in both combat and training. This item is Code B, not approved for service use.

 (E06012) CTG 6.8MM SPECIAL PURPOSE 4SP/1TRCR LINKED (XM1184/XM1187) is a 6.8mm Ball Cartridge / Special Purpose (SP) ammunition packed linked belts with a 6.8mm GP Tracer Cartridge for use
 in the Next Generation Squad Weapons (NGSW) M250 Automatic Rifle. The XM1184 SP Ball Cartridges utilizes projectiles with an exposed tip surrounded by a copper jacket. The M1187 GP Tracer has a steel
 penetrator surrounded by a thick-based jacket with a cavity packed with tracer material which lights upon firing. This ammunition is intended for use against a broad spectrum of hard targets. This is a combat-
 only war reserve item. This item is Code B, not approved for service use.

 (E06014) CTG 6.8MM REDUCED RANGE ROUND (XM1188) is a 6.8mm Ball Cartridge; a training standard item used for training purposes. The ammunition is packed in cartons for use in the NGSW M7 Rifle/
 XM8 Carbine. The Cartridge is intended to perform similarly to the combat variants and is intended for use on military installations including those with Surface Danger Zone (SDZ) restrictions. This item is Code
 B, not approved for service use.

 (E06015) CTG 6.8MM SPECIAL PURPOSE ROUND (XM1184) is a 6.8mm Ball Cartridge. The Special Purpose (SP) ammunition is packed in cartons for use in the NGSW M7 Rifle/XM8 Carbine. The SP Ball
 Cartridge utilizes projectiles with an exposed tip surrounded by a copper jacket. This ammunition is intended for use against a broad spectrum of hard targets. The SP ammunition is a combat-only war reserve
 item. This item is Code B, not approved for service use.

 (E06016) CTG 6.8MM GENERAL PURPOSE 4GP/1TRCR LINKED (M1186/XM1187) is a 6.8mm Ball Cartridge / General Purpose (GP) ammunition packed linked belts with a 6.8mm GP Tracer Cartridge for
 use in the Next Generation Squad Weapons (NGSW) Automatic Rifle. The M1186 GP Ball Cartridges has a steel penetrator and non-lead slug surrounded by a copper jacket. The M1187 Tracer Cartridge has a
 steel penetrator surrounded by a thick-based jacket with a cavity packed with tracer material which lights upon firing. This ammunition is intended for use against personnel and light-armored targets. The GP and
 Tracer ammunition are training standard items used in both combat and training. This item is Code B, not approved for service use.
