 and within urban structures. The XM1204 HEAB-T consists of a titanium and steel with preformed fragments body, glass reinforced Ultem rotating band, multi-mode electro-mechanical programmable contact set
 fuze, pyrotechnic tracer, double base or extruded propellant, an M36A2 percussion primer, and steel cartridge case. The XM1204 is planned to be packed 10 cartridges to a PA191 ammunition container. Uses a
 FY 2019 Defense Ordnance Technology Consortium (DOTC) Middle Tier Acquisition- Rapid Prototyping (MTA-RP) program to support the Optionally Manned Fighting Vehicle (OMFV) program and transition to
 Milestone C in Quarter two FY 2027 and Low Rate Initial Production in Quarter three FY 2027. These items are Code B, not approved for service use.




